Moody's Investors Service Inc said itmay downgrade Service Merchandise Co's 300 mln dlrs of Ba-2senior subordinated notes.    The rating agency said it had anticipated that ServiceMerchandise would be able to achieve better operating resultsthan it actually did in fiscal 1986.    Moody's said it would assess future prospects for thecompany, as well as for the whole catalogue showroom industry.The agency will also examine the effects of recent acquisitionson Service Merchandise's operating results, financial structureand cash flow. Reuter&#3;